item.title: CVE-2022-2421|2024-08-03T00:39:07.623Z -- socket.io -- socket.io-parser
item.description: Due to improper type validation in attachment parsing the Socket.io js library, it is possible to overwrite the _placeholder object which allows an attacker to place references to functions at arbitrary places in the resulting query object.
